1
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:29,780
[Episode 27]

2
00:01:47,719 --> 00:01:48,940
<i>Miao Jing, over at Hongshen...</i>

3
00:01:48,940 --> 00:01:51,220
Miao Jing's been dealing
with a family emergency recently.

4
00:01:51,220 --> 00:01:54,439
- Could I ask for two days off for her?
<i>- Sure.</i>

5
00:01:54,439 --> 00:01:57,573
<i>- May I ask how she's doing?</i>
- You may not.

6
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:01,376
Sorry to trouble you.

7
00:02:29,426 --> 00:02:31,966
No vehicles or refrigerated coffins available?

8
00:02:33,180 --> 00:02:37,300
Then I'll arrange a vehicle myself.
We'll send her over today.

9
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,660
[Contact, Bo]

10
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:48,040
[Contact, Uncle Zhou]

11
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,720
[Call Home Phone]

12
00:02:55,041 --> 00:02:56,520
Uncle Zhou.

13
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:22,550
I'm sorry for your loss.

14
00:03:24,180 --> 00:03:26,900
Thank you, Uncle Zhou.
Where did you borrow the vehicle from?

15
00:03:26,900 --> 00:03:28,541
The owner of Final Stop.

16
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:32,093
We've borrowed their hearse
with a refrigerated casket before.

17
00:03:34,101 --> 00:03:35,860
You've been up all night.

18
00:03:35,860 --> 00:03:39,673
You must be starving.
Here. Have something to eat.

19
00:03:44,161 --> 00:03:46,100
Eat even if you don't feel like it.

20
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:48,120
There's a lot of hard work ahead.

21
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:50,821
Don't wear yourself out.

22
00:03:50,821 --> 00:03:52,001
Don't worry.

23
00:03:52,001 --> 00:03:53,986
We're here with you.

24
00:03:54,830 --> 00:03:56,360
Thank you, Uncle Zhou.

25
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:58,300
We'll take her to the morgue first.

26
00:03:58,300 --> 00:04:00,800
Okay. Han. Thanks for the help.

27
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:02,453
- Okay.
- This way.

28
00:04:15,260 --> 00:04:16,880
Family members, please confirm the body.

29
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:20,766
Then sign the handover paperwork
and the death certificate.

30
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:35,080
I'll go.

31
00:04:38,661 --> 00:04:40,360
I can do it.

32
00:06:07,981 --> 00:06:09,886
Have you confirmed it?

33
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:22,933
Then come sign here.

34
00:06:40,380 --> 00:06:42,866
We also need your fingerprint.

35
00:06:54,021 --> 00:06:55,710
Miao Jing.

36
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:14,680
[Soiled Utility Room]

37
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:23,281
My chest felt so tight just now.

38
00:07:23,281 --> 00:07:24,639
Let's go.

39
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:36,420
[Hall of Remembrance]

40
00:07:36,420 --> 00:07:40,480
[Farewell Ceremony for Ms. Wei Ming Zhen]

41
00:07:47,660 --> 00:07:50,701
The farewell ceremony will begin shortly.

42
00:07:50,701 --> 00:07:54,973
Family and friends, please come to the front.

43
00:07:55,661 --> 00:07:59,993
Family and friends, please come to the front.

44
00:08:02,701 --> 00:08:06,013
Immediate family in the first row.

45
00:08:06,961 --> 00:08:09,873
Immediate family in the first row.

46
00:08:14,740 --> 00:08:19,660
Today, we gather here with the deepest sorrow

47
00:08:19,660 --> 00:08:22,660
to hold this farewell ceremony.

48
00:08:22,660 --> 00:08:26,280
We mourn the loss of Ms. Wei Ming Zhen.

49
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:31,120
We bid Ms. Wei Ming Zhen a heartfelt farewell
on her final journey.

50
00:08:39,441 --> 00:08:42,460
Moment of silence.

51
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:49,366
The moment of silence is over.

52
00:08:52,201 --> 00:08:58,440
Now, let us bow three times
to Ms. Wei Ming Zhen,

53
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:02,195
to express our grief.

54
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:09,940
Everyone, first bow.

55
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:14,390
Wei Ming Zhen is dead?

56
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,973
Who are you?

57
00:09:24,140 --> 00:09:27,581
You're Wei Ming Zhen's daughter, right?
Your mother owed us over 200,000 yuan.

58
00:09:27,581 --> 00:09:30,760
Then she just dies and walks away.

59
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:36,806
Whatever the reason,
causing trouble at a funeral isn't appropriate.

60
00:09:37,681 --> 00:09:40,420
Decency won't pay her debts.

61
00:09:40,420 --> 00:09:43,601
If I don't corner you now,
I may never find you again.

62
00:09:43,601 --> 00:09:47,640
I know people like you too well.
You think death wipes the slate clean.

63
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:49,320
Not a chance.

64
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:51,273
If you want to talk, do it outside.

65
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,594
Trying to run? Let go.

66
00:09:55,594 --> 00:09:57,720
Don't push your luck.

67
00:10:06,421 --> 00:10:09,520
- How much did she owe you?
- 230,000 yuan.

68
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:13,060
She signed the IOU last July.
It's two months overdue.

69
00:10:13,060 --> 00:10:15,440
How did you find this place?

70
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:16,961
Her phone was disconnected.

71
00:10:16,961 --> 00:10:20,620
The contract listed her daughter's information.
That means you.

72
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:23,359
How do we know you didn't hear the news
and plan to run?

73
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:28,640
Look, we really did lend the money out.

74
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:33,441
If we hadn't been unable to find her,
we wouldn't be here at a time like this.

75
00:10:33,441 --> 00:10:35,126
Where is the contract?

76
00:10:42,140 --> 00:10:44,726
It's okay. Just a copy. Give it to him.

77
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:54,320
[Loan Agreement]

78
00:10:59,341 --> 00:11:02,780
Borrow one, pay back two.
That's loan-shark interest.

79
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:06,780
This contract is illegal.

80
00:11:06,780 --> 00:11:11,104
And now that she's dead,
her debt has nothing to do with me.

81
00:11:12,301 --> 00:11:14,996
It's illegal just because you say so?

82
00:11:18,340 --> 00:11:21,480
Showing up to intimidate people.
Harassing the neighbors.

83
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:23,760
Making personal threats.

84
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:27,013
I know all your tricks inside and out.

85
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,620
I don't have time for this.

86
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:35,733
If you know what's good for you, get out.

87
00:11:37,421 --> 00:11:39,960
You punk.
Who do you think you're pushing around?

88
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:41,820
- Boss!
- It hurts! It hurts.

89
00:11:41,820 --> 00:11:43,640
Let go.

90
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,921
- It hurts!
- If you keep causing trouble,

91
00:11:45,921 --> 00:11:47,701
we'll call the police.

92
00:11:47,701 --> 00:11:49,020
Go ahead. Call the police.

93
00:11:49,020 --> 00:11:51,201
I've got a promissory note and a contract.
You think I'm scared? That hurts!

94
00:11:51,201 --> 00:11:53,920
- Boss!
- I am the police.

95
00:11:55,380 --> 00:11:56,940
What's going on?

96
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:07,040
A promissory note and a contract.

97
00:12:15,701 --> 00:12:17,660
This is loan sharking.

98
00:12:17,660 --> 00:12:19,601
The law won't protect it.

99
00:12:19,601 --> 00:12:21,620
You borrow money, you pay it back.

100
00:12:21,620 --> 00:12:23,981
Officer, we're not running a charity.

101
00:12:23,981 --> 00:12:28,806
Wei Ming Zhen may be dead,
but her daughter has to pay it back, right?

102
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,700
They can repay the principal.

103
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:36,000
The contract says borrow one, pay back two.
That part doesn't count.

104
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:40,540
Loan sharking is a civil offense.
I can't detain you right now.

105
00:12:40,540 --> 00:12:43,040
But while collecting illegal interest,

106
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:46,940
if you endanger their safety or property,

107
00:12:46,940 --> 00:12:51,900
the police can punish you under the law.

108
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:55,133
What? Want to come back to the station with me?

109
00:12:55,821 --> 00:12:57,400
Uncle Zhou.

110
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,700
You should go home.

111
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:02,660
You have my contact information.
I'm not going anywhere.

112
00:13:02,660 --> 00:13:04,880
We'll work out a plan later and settle this.

113
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:08,833
But if you come back and cause trouble,
I won't go easy on you.

114
00:13:10,380 --> 00:13:11,943
Get out of here.

115
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:15,280
Contact me.

116
00:13:18,820 --> 00:13:20,020
Go.

117
00:13:21,681 --> 00:13:23,626
You should've hit him!

118
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:28,755
It's all right now.

119
00:13:29,860 --> 00:13:32,260
A senior family member needs to be present
during the cremation.

120
00:13:32,260 --> 00:13:34,013
I need to go in.

121
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:49,839
Not until I saw her portrait just now
did it really feel like she was gone.

122
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:06,699
Miao Jing.

123
00:14:07,780 --> 00:14:09,613
Don't force yourself.

124
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:18,800
These past two days,
I've kept thinking about the past.

125
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:23,900
About how she picked me up
from my aunt's place,

126
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:27,080
and ended my days of living off relatives.

127
00:14:27,784 --> 00:14:29,421
She brought me to Teng City.

128
00:14:29,421 --> 00:14:31,040
Then I met you.

129
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:33,285
She gave me a home.

130
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,612
She bought me dresses.

131
00:14:36,612 --> 00:14:38,212
She packed eggs for me.

132
00:14:38,212 --> 00:14:39,795
She bought me gold jewelry.

133
00:14:41,860 --> 00:14:45,940
It feels like all I can remember
is the good in her.

134
00:14:45,940 --> 00:14:48,260
The bad parts of her...

135
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:51,343
I seem to have forgotten them all.

136
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:58,189
Do you think she came to me
because she really missed me,

137
00:14:58,189 --> 00:15:01,153
or because she needed me to handle all this?

138
00:15:13,253 --> 00:15:14,680
Miao Jing.

139
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:17,620
We're all ordinary people.

140
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:23,020
It's normal to feel upset
when something like this happens.

141
00:15:23,020 --> 00:15:24,813
It doesn't prove anything.

142
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:27,084
What happened before,

143
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:31,326
good or bad, is already in the past.

144
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:35,406
The joy.

145
00:15:36,581 --> 00:15:38,340
The pain.

146
00:15:38,340 --> 00:15:40,703
Don't force yourself to choose.

147
00:15:52,061 --> 00:15:54,860
The family can place the burial items
in this box.

148
00:15:54,860 --> 00:15:58,420
After cremation, it'll be returned
with the urn.

149
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,940
[Trolley Forward]

150
00:17:47,260 --> 00:17:50,100
I never had the luck to change my fate.

151
00:17:50,100 --> 00:17:54,340
But now I have the power

152
00:17:55,260 --> 00:17:59,866
to show you what it's like
to have more money than you can spend.

153
00:18:06,961 --> 00:18:08,660
This is for you.

154
00:18:08,660 --> 00:18:12,459
Zhai. There's one more thing I need from you.

155
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:19,153
Help me see this path clearly,
so nothing goes wrong.

156
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:27,606
Mr. Zhang.

157
00:18:31,141 --> 00:18:32,901
Mr. Liu sent word.

158
00:18:32,901 --> 00:18:36,460
He says once this blows over, we can
officially start shipping early next month.

159
00:18:36,460 --> 00:18:39,660
- It's just...
- Just what?

160
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:44,040
The police have been watching closely.
What happened in Lingang was so sudden.

161
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:48,400
Do you think
the police may have found out something?

162
00:18:50,020 --> 00:18:52,831
Sorry, Mr. Zhang. I spoke out of turn.

163
00:18:54,780 --> 00:18:56,300
Six years.

164
00:18:57,600 --> 00:19:02,660
Zhou Kang An hasn't taken his eyes off us.

165
00:19:02,660 --> 00:19:04,441
Right?

166
00:19:04,441 --> 00:19:06,567
I'm used to it.

167
00:19:08,260 --> 00:19:09,595
Zhai.

168
00:19:10,621 --> 00:19:13,837
This time, I took the hit for you.

169
00:19:14,780 --> 00:19:16,613
Now I don't owe you anything.

170
00:19:25,260 --> 00:19:27,800
[Kuangxia Real Estate]

171
00:19:29,981 --> 00:19:34,040
Let me tell you. I used to eat inside a tent.

172
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:36,511
Never on the roadside.

173
00:19:39,417 --> 00:19:41,481
What the heck...

174
00:19:41,481 --> 00:19:46,540
If Mr. Zhai were still around,
they wouldn't stand a chance.

175
00:19:46,540 --> 00:19:48,421
Who knew I'd end up like this?

176
00:19:48,421 --> 00:19:49,861
Eat up.

177
00:19:49,861 --> 00:19:53,003
It's got dust on it. I'm not eating.

178
00:20:19,941 --> 00:20:24,100
Tomorrow I'll find a storage place
and leave the ashes there for now.

179
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:28,300
Then over the weekend,
I'll check out the cemetery here.

180
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:30,580
No need to go to all that trouble.

181
00:20:30,580 --> 00:20:34,066
The ashes can stay here for now.

182
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:41,251
What are your plans?

183
00:20:43,300 --> 00:20:47,440
What else can I do? I still have to go to work.

184
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:50,861
Cen Ye is back. There's a lot to deal with.

185
00:20:50,861 --> 00:20:53,040
Maybe you should head back first.

186
00:20:57,220 --> 00:21:00,421
It's fine. Get some rest.

187
00:21:00,421 --> 00:21:03,620
If anything comes up, call me anytime.

188
00:21:20,361 --> 00:21:24,759
- I'll walk you out.
- No, I'll take a cab.

189
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:36,100
[Melatonin Tablets]

190
00:21:37,780 --> 00:21:40,813
[5:00]

191
00:22:16,941 --> 00:22:19,580
Therefore, based on our investigation,

192
00:22:19,580 --> 00:22:24,481
the third-party partner represented by Liu
has questionable qualifications.

193
00:22:24,481 --> 00:22:28,580
- They may have engaged in business misconduct.
- Sorry.

194
00:22:28,580 --> 00:22:32,520
We know Mr. Liu's situation.
But those are all legacy procedural issues.

195
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:34,641
We can definitely settle this within the month.

196
00:22:34,641 --> 00:22:38,200
Could Hongshen hold off
on reporting this for now?

197
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:42,100
I understand your concerns.
But the audit procedure--

198
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:45,361
If we could speed up this process,
would we still need to sit here and talk?

199
00:22:45,361 --> 00:22:47,566
That isn't their call.

200
00:22:48,361 --> 00:22:50,130
Let's keep going.

201
00:22:51,540 --> 00:22:54,160
I'll explain the details to you later.

202
00:22:57,500 --> 00:23:00,257
This isn't part of your job, is it?

203
00:23:02,340 --> 00:23:04,029
Let's keep going.

204
00:23:08,901 --> 00:23:10,164
Okay.

205
00:23:29,060 --> 00:23:31,833
Are things at home still difficult?

206
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:37,255
No. It's mostly taken care of.

207
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:41,881
You can take a few days off and get some rest.

208
00:23:41,881 --> 00:23:46,560
No need. If there's nothing else for me to do,
I'll get going.

209
00:24:00,660 --> 00:24:02,540
[Teng City Teng'an Cemetery]

210
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:10,300
[About Teng City Teng'an Cemetery]

211
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:23,461
You haven't been eating properly lately.
Cold drinks are hard on your stomach.

212
00:24:23,461 --> 00:24:25,026
Have something warm.

213
00:24:37,820 --> 00:24:40,646
You're not working overtime this weekend,
are you?

214
00:24:40,646 --> 00:24:42,073
Why?

215
00:24:43,180 --> 00:24:47,100
I booked the tickets.
I'm taking you out for a change of scenery.

216
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:48,594
Where to?

217
00:24:51,121 --> 00:24:52,623
Jiang City.

218
00:24:58,780 --> 00:25:01,432
- If you don't want to go--
- Let's go.

219
00:25:37,100 --> 00:25:38,617
Come in.

220
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:45,860
Bin.

221
00:25:45,860 --> 00:25:48,160
I'd like to take a couple of days off.

222
00:25:51,880 --> 00:25:54,540
I'll make sure someone watches the route.

223
00:25:54,540 --> 00:25:56,900
The emergency plans are all in place, too.

224
00:25:56,900 --> 00:25:58,981
As long as work is covered.

225
00:25:58,981 --> 00:26:01,493
Just don't drop the ball elsewhere.

226
00:26:04,280 --> 00:26:05,706
Go ahead.

227
00:26:19,540 --> 00:26:21,000
<i>I'll be gone for a few days.</i>

228
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:23,580
<i>Keep an eye on Zhang Bin's people.</i>

229
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:26,960
[Message, Uncle Zhou]

230
00:26:33,521 --> 00:26:36,080
Mr. Zhang. The site is causing trouble again.

231
00:26:36,080 --> 00:26:38,260
They even put up banners
and tried to protest downstairs.

232
00:26:38,260 --> 00:26:40,220
It's been handled.

233
00:26:43,340 --> 00:26:46,020
They were acting on impulse.

234
00:26:46,020 --> 00:26:51,326
If loyalty could put food on the table,
he wouldn't be here causing trouble.

235
00:26:52,540 --> 00:26:54,020
Remember this.

236
00:26:54,020 --> 00:26:57,480
Never be the kind of person
who is blindly loyal

237
00:26:57,480 --> 00:26:59,640
but not very bright.

238
00:27:07,621 --> 00:27:11,461
Why does Chen Yi take a personal leave now?

239
00:27:11,461 --> 00:27:13,766
Didn't you just see him?

240
00:27:16,240 --> 00:27:19,121
Wasn't he supposed to lead the convoy
on the site visit?

241
00:27:19,121 --> 00:27:21,201
And he just walks out now?

242
00:27:21,201 --> 00:27:23,120
Just the opposite.

243
00:27:23,809 --> 00:27:28,526
This is the perfect opening to draw him away.

244
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:31,847
This way.

245
00:27:53,580 --> 00:27:54,621
I checked.

246
00:27:54,621 --> 00:27:58,440
This bus route is the same one you took
when you first came to Teng City.

247
00:27:58,440 --> 00:28:02,213
Only it gets there an hour earlier.
We'll arrive this afternoon.

248
00:28:05,621 --> 00:28:07,320
Give me the bag.

249
00:28:08,340 --> 00:28:12,366
After all, she was the one who brought me here.

250
00:28:28,260 --> 00:28:32,320
Passengers for Jiang City,
line up here for ticket check.

251
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:35,121
Any passengers for Jiang City?

252
00:28:35,121 --> 00:28:37,313
Anyone else for Jiang City?

253
00:28:39,820 --> 00:28:42,919
Over there is fine too.
Both ticket gates are open.

254
00:28:49,381 --> 00:28:50,401
Keep your hands to yourself.

255
00:28:50,401 --> 00:28:52,661
How was I supposed to know
you'd bring an urn on the bus?

256
00:28:52,661 --> 00:28:54,874
That is seriously bad luck.

257
00:28:57,621 --> 00:28:59,361
Make way.

258
00:28:59,361 --> 00:29:00,580
Sir, let go.

259
00:29:00,580 --> 00:29:01,681
What is going on?

260
00:29:01,681 --> 00:29:03,381
He was going through my bag.
I caught him red-handed.

261
00:29:03,381 --> 00:29:04,481
I didn't.

262
00:29:04,481 --> 00:29:06,360
Your identification and tickets, please.

263
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:07,780
Documents.

264
00:29:07,780 --> 00:29:09,666
Okay. Let me find them.

265
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:12,820
Stop right there.

266
00:29:12,820 --> 00:29:14,880
Trying to run? Stop. Come with us.

267
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:17,020
First thing in the morning,
I run into two people off to a funeral.

268
00:29:17,020 --> 00:29:19,100
- Watch your mouth.
- What a nightmare.

269
00:29:19,100 --> 00:29:20,492
Move.

270
00:29:21,540 --> 00:29:22,701
Move.

271
00:29:22,701 --> 00:29:24,753
What kind of people are they?

272
00:29:25,474 --> 00:29:26,727
Seriously.

273
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:29,921
They even brought an urn with them.

274
00:29:29,921 --> 00:29:32,040
What terrible luck.

275
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:38,040
[Teng City to Jiang City]

276
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:53,650
It's too crowded in there. I'll hold it.

277
00:29:59,361 --> 00:30:02,633
You got up early. Get some sleep.
I'll wake you when we arrive.

278
00:30:32,901 --> 00:30:34,532
You're awake.

279
00:30:35,840 --> 00:30:38,020
Did you sleep well?

280
00:30:38,020 --> 00:30:39,865
Very well.

281
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:44,284
Then this pillow could fetch a good price.

282
00:30:45,800 --> 00:30:48,187
A really good price.

283
00:30:54,603 --> 00:30:56,446
Have something to eat.

284
00:30:59,780 --> 00:31:01,360
What's wrong?

285
00:31:03,721 --> 00:31:05,548
You're so good to me.

286
00:31:07,763 --> 00:31:09,902
One sausage, and suddenly I'm good to you?

287
00:31:13,161 --> 00:31:15,222
This is already great.

288
00:31:16,721 --> 00:31:20,365
All right. I'll bring you more next time.

289
00:31:31,641 --> 00:31:33,624
Jiang City is huge.

290
00:31:39,460 --> 00:31:41,166
We're almost there.

291
00:32:02,240 --> 00:32:04,015
Does any of it look familiar?

292
00:32:05,098 --> 00:32:07,180
I was too little when I came here.

293
00:32:07,180 --> 00:32:09,401
I don't remember any of it.

294
00:32:09,401 --> 00:32:11,090
Then I'll scout the way.

295
00:32:12,100 --> 00:32:13,740
The exit is over there.

296
00:32:13,740 --> 00:32:14,901
Slow down.

297
00:32:14,901 --> 00:32:17,600
Need a taxi? Taxi rides here.

298
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:19,513
- Don't rush.
- Taxi!

299
00:32:21,441 --> 00:32:24,820
Handsome guy, pretty lady.
Need a ride? Where are you headed?

300
00:32:24,820 --> 00:32:28,340
- When was this place renovated?
- About five years ago.

301
00:32:28,340 --> 00:32:31,720
I thought you were tourists.
You're locals? Back visiting family?

302
00:32:31,720 --> 00:32:34,481
I stayed here for a while as a kid.

303
00:32:34,481 --> 00:32:36,181
Can we go to Nanshan Cemetery?

304
00:32:36,181 --> 00:32:37,881
Nanshan Cemetery is pretty far.

305
00:32:37,881 --> 00:32:39,100
But don't worry.

306
00:32:39,100 --> 00:32:41,140
We're not picky. We'll go anywhere.

307
00:32:41,140 --> 00:32:43,979
Need a private ride?

308
00:32:58,441 --> 00:33:01,820
Do you want to see your relatives here?

309
00:33:01,820 --> 00:33:04,681
No. I only have an aunt here.

310
00:33:04,681 --> 00:33:08,700
When I was little, my mother dumped me on them.

311
00:33:08,700 --> 00:33:11,201
But they didn't want me either.

312
00:33:11,201 --> 00:33:16,899
So to Wei Ming Zhen and to me,
they were never family.

313
00:33:19,040 --> 00:33:20,831
Then it's better not to see them.

314
00:33:21,780 --> 00:33:24,509
What made you decide
to come to Jiang City with me?

315
00:33:25,981 --> 00:33:29,660
You went straight back to work
as soon as you returned.

316
00:33:29,660 --> 00:33:31,773
Getting out for a while will do you good.

317
00:33:32,540 --> 00:33:36,286
Besides,
everyone deserves to return home in the end.

318
00:33:43,421 --> 00:33:46,394
You haven't slept well
these past few days, have you?

319
00:33:47,859 --> 00:33:52,406
Bringing Wei back can put your mind at ease.

320
00:33:54,141 --> 00:33:55,440
Thank you.

321
00:33:57,040 --> 00:33:58,573
Don't be silly.

322
00:34:28,540 --> 00:34:32,241
This is the burial plot you reserved.

323
00:34:32,241 --> 00:34:34,981
It's quiet here, with a wide-open view.

324
00:34:34,981 --> 00:34:37,261
The cemetery facilities are also very complete.

325
00:34:37,261 --> 00:34:40,080
From custom headstones
to routine cleaning and upkeep,

326
00:34:40,080 --> 00:34:42,760
we provide all maintenance services.

327
00:34:42,760 --> 00:34:45,308
So you don't have to worry about that.

328
00:35:07,200 --> 00:35:10,424
We'll seal the grave now.
Family members, please step back.

329
00:35:29,761 --> 00:35:31,462
My condolences.

330
00:35:35,020 --> 00:35:36,780
We'll get going.

331
00:35:50,361 --> 00:35:52,740
In a way, she came home in the end.

332
00:35:57,481 --> 00:35:59,386
Came home in the end.

333
00:36:13,700 --> 00:36:18,780
[Beloved Mother Wei Ming Zhen]
[Erected by her devoted daughter, Miao Jing]

334
00:36:18,780 --> 00:36:21,440
When I was little, I lived here.

335
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:24,724
It always snowed here in winter.

336
00:36:24,724 --> 00:36:27,440
The snow would be ankle-deep.

337
00:36:29,580 --> 00:36:32,980
In Teng City, winter was just endless rain.

338
00:36:34,560 --> 00:36:38,300
So when I first moved there, it felt strange.

339
00:36:38,300 --> 00:36:40,973
Why didn't they have winter there?

340
00:36:41,640 --> 00:36:45,860
When I lived here,
winter was my favorite season.

341
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:51,461
In winter,
I could sneak out and play in the snow.

342
00:36:51,461 --> 00:36:55,715
And once winter came, New Year was almost here.

343
00:36:57,465 --> 00:36:59,760
Every New Year,

344
00:37:00,381 --> 00:37:05,013
the other kids
would get new clothes from their moms.

345
00:37:06,281 --> 00:37:08,026
But I didn't.

346
00:37:10,180 --> 00:37:14,341
I remember always sitting on my aunt's doorstep

347
00:37:14,341 --> 00:37:16,520
watching and waiting,

348
00:37:17,610 --> 00:37:19,740
waiting for my mom to come get me.

349
00:37:21,240 --> 00:37:24,053
But she never came.

350
00:37:28,481 --> 00:37:30,200
Then one day,

351
00:37:31,220 --> 00:37:33,619
when she finally did,

352
00:37:34,801 --> 00:37:37,401
she said to me,

353
00:37:37,401 --> 00:37:41,485
"Jing, I'm taking you with me."

354
00:37:42,680 --> 00:37:44,682
"We have a home now."

355
00:37:46,241 --> 00:37:49,113
You have no idea how happy I was.

356
00:37:51,461 --> 00:37:53,257
But then,

357
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:57,806
she left me somewhere else.

358
00:38:11,140 --> 00:38:15,140
[Garden of Grace]

359
00:38:24,921 --> 00:38:26,513
Chen Yi.

360
00:38:29,301 --> 00:38:31,631
I really don't have a mom anymore.

361
00:38:43,720 --> 00:38:45,373
I'm here.

362
00:38:48,420 --> 00:38:54,420
[Garden of Grace]

363
00:39:06,460 --> 00:39:11,180
[Little Alley Restaurant]

364
00:39:18,200 --> 00:39:20,640
Maybe we should stay.

365
00:39:20,640 --> 00:39:23,192
Wouldn't it be nice to live here?

366
00:39:26,580 --> 00:39:27,913
We could.

367
00:39:30,201 --> 00:39:34,593
Then tell me what I can do here.

368
00:39:36,140 --> 00:39:38,660
Nothing, if you want.

369
00:39:38,660 --> 00:39:40,600
So you're supporting me again?

370
00:39:40,600 --> 00:39:43,106
I'm not. I couldn't afford you.

371
00:39:48,340 --> 00:39:53,461
In Jiang City,
we could open a little shop like this.

372
00:39:53,461 --> 00:39:55,573
Open 24 hours a day.

373
00:39:56,220 --> 00:39:59,580
You'd take the day shift. I'd take nights.

374
00:39:59,580 --> 00:40:02,960
In the storage room, we'd set up a little cot.

375
00:40:02,960 --> 00:40:04,560
We'd save on rent.

376
00:40:04,560 --> 00:40:06,463
And have three steady meals a day.

377
00:40:10,481 --> 00:40:12,035
Sounds good.

378
00:40:12,741 --> 00:40:14,620
But what about you?

379
00:40:14,620 --> 00:40:19,941
You said before that paying for my education
was a long-term investment.

380
00:40:19,941 --> 00:40:25,241
You said that I had to move to a better city
and find a good job.

381
00:40:25,241 --> 00:40:30,885
If we just stay here and open a little shop,
wouldn't your investment be a bust?

382
00:40:32,500 --> 00:40:36,080
Did I really say
something that awful back then?

383
00:40:36,080 --> 00:40:38,040
You said plenty.

384
00:40:41,340 --> 00:40:43,793
Then I really was a jerk.

385
00:41:14,880 --> 00:41:18,420
[Little Alley Restaurant]

386
00:41:39,580 --> 00:41:43,280
[Answer, Decline]

387
00:42:19,680 --> 00:42:22,241
What a pretty lady and a handsome man.

388
00:42:22,241 --> 00:42:24,741
Are you two here on your honeymoon?

389
00:42:24,741 --> 00:42:26,660
It's the Mid-Autumn Festival in a few days.

390
00:42:26,660 --> 00:42:29,540
Young man,
buy your beautiful wife a gold necklace.

391
00:42:29,540 --> 00:42:31,640
It'd be so festive.

392
00:42:31,640 --> 00:42:33,193
Do you like it?

393
00:42:33,881 --> 00:42:37,743
Can we really afford to buy gold
for Mid-Autumn Festival...

394
00:42:40,301 --> 00:42:42,281
Why ask your wife?

395
00:42:42,281 --> 00:42:45,260
If you buy it for her, she'll be thrilled.

396
00:42:45,260 --> 00:42:47,443
I'm not in charge of the money.

397
00:42:47,443 --> 00:42:49,060
Of course.

398
00:42:49,060 --> 00:42:51,652
Just let me know if you need anything.

399
00:42:51,652 --> 00:42:53,606
- Okay, thanks.
- Sure.

400
00:42:54,660 --> 00:42:55,920
Let's go.

